file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        successful: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        attach_info: {type: string}
        attachments: {type: string}
        attachments_md5: {type: string}
        attachments_sha1: {type: string}
        attachments_sha256: {type: string}
        cc: {type: string}
        date: {type: string}
        error: {type: string}
        headers: {type: string}
        html_body: {type: string}
        id: {type: string}
        o365_id: {type: string}
        raw_content: {type: string}
        raw_headers: {type: string}
        recipients: {type: string}
        reply_to: {type: string}
        result: {type: string}
        rtf_body: {type: string}
        sender: {type: string}
        subject: {type: string}
        text_body: {type: string}
        type: {type: string}
        valid_recipients_email: {type: string}
        valid_reply_to_email: {type: string}
        valid_sender_email: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp2:
      properties:
        response: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes: {}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of Microsoft Office 365
  title: Microsoft Office 365
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Deletes an email message
      parameters:
      - description: O365 ID of message to delete.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: O365 ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Office 365 Delete Mail
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Get email messages
      parameters:
      - description: Count of emails to get, max 250
        example: ''
        in: body
        name: Count
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: A csv of extensions you would like to ignore. Useful if image
          files are being parsed out of email footer as attachments. Default is .jp(e)g,
          .png, .gif. Filling this value will OVERWRITE existing default
        example: .jpeg,.png,.exe,.gif
        in: query
        name: exclude extensions
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Ignore errors parsing an email. Defaults to False
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Ignore Errors
        required: false
        schema: {type: boolean}
      - description: Marks the emails as read
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Mark Read
        required: true
        schema: {type: boolean}
      - description: Offset value from the most recent messages to start getting messages
          from
        example: ''
        in: body
        name: Count offset
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Optional search query to filter with
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Search Query
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Retrieve only unread emails
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Unread
        required: true
        schema: {type: boolean}
      - description: Retrieve attachments from emails
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: With attachments
        required: true
        schema: {type: boolean}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Office 365 Get and Search Mail
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: Set an email message as read
      parameters:
      - description: ID of message to mark read
        example: 45sgs654%srfhsv
        in: query
        name: Message ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Office 365 Mark Message as Read
tags:
- {name: Communication}
